Decision tree

  • Discuss Oroboros methods based on the assumption that sample is not going to be enough
    • If each region weights enough:
      • Half of the lizards tested for respiration and ATP synthesis, half for ROS (one machine per lizard, each chamber per each region) - X
      • For each lizard, we will measure ROS of one region and ATP of the other in a randomize way - V
    • If weight per regions is not enough:
      • Pool different regions and measure both respiration and ROS - 3 lizard per measurement = 24 lizards per treatment so we obtain 8 measures of ROS and 8 of respiration per treatment - V
      • Find other ways to measure ROS and use Oroboros only for respiration (homogenates of tissue may involve less mitochondrial loss)
